 {"id":"bd-a46q1","title":"feature(pane-validation): comprehensive correctness, parity, and soak testing","description":"Goal\n- Build a complete validation harness for pane behavior across runtimes.\n\nWhat this feature owns\n- Unit/property/fuzz tests for core model + contract.\n- PTY E2E suite for terminal interactions.\n- Browser E2E suite for wasm/web interactions.\n- Cross-host parity trace runner and diff reports.\n\nDefinition of done\n- Deterministic test evidence proves correctness and parity.\n- Soak/stress tests catch race-like and long-run regressions.","design":"Validation strategy\n- Treat deterministic replay as the spine: all E2E/perf/parity checks should consume or emit semantic traces.\n- Use layered confidence: property/fuzz at core, host E2E at adapters, parity at cross-host integration, soak for longevity.\n- Every flaky or non-deterministic failure must produce a minimized repro artifact.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Full validation pyramid exists: unit/property/fuzz, PTY/web E2E, parity, soak.\n2) Canonical E2E scripts run locally/CI with consistent arguments and outputs.\n3) Structured observability schema + artifact bundles support deterministic failure triage.\n4) Validation outputs gate rollout decisions with explicit thresholds.","notes":"Execution lane: Track E (validation/observability spine).\nPrimary sequence: observability foundation bd-a46q1.7 -> bd-a46q1.8 -> bd-a46q1.9, then validation suites bd-a46q1.1/.2/.3/.4/.5/.6.\nUser impact: high confidence that behavior is correct, deterministic, and debuggable.\nEvidence required: structured log schema, artifact bundles, parity runner outputs, and soak diagnostics.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","estimated_minutes":1890,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:30:50.924858656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-11T07:29:01.629711890Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","pane","parity","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1","