 {"id":"bd-a46q1.6","title":"task(pane-validation): add long-run soak, stress, and chaos scenarios with flake triage workflow","description":"Background\n- Pane systems can degrade over time under repeated interactions, rapid resize storms, and host interruption events.\n\nScope\n- Add soak tests that run prolonged random-but-valid interaction streams.\n- Add stress scenarios for rapid viewport changes, repeated split/close churn, and large tree depth/width.\n- Define flake triage and quarantine process with reproducibility requirements and ownership.\n\nAcceptance\n- Soak/stress runs are part of reliability validation with actionable output artifacts.\n- Intermittent failures are tracked via explicit triage workflow rather than ignored.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Implement scoped validation capability with reproducible execution and deterministic assertions.\n2) Add/maintain runner scripts for local+CI with explicit modes (smoke/full/stress) where applicable.\n3) Produce structured logs and artifact bundles (trace, snapshots, metadata) for every failure.\n4) Document pass/fail criteria and ensure outputs are actionable without ad-hoc reruns.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:37:17.859537226Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-11T07:27:35.505154885Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["chaos","pane","soak","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-14w4r","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-11T05:37:38.123536169Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2bav7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-11T05:37:37.752332732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-a46q1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-11T05:37:17.859537226Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.6","de