 {"id":"bd-a46q1.7","title":"task(pane-validation): implement structured test observability schema and artifact contract","description":"Background\n- Reliable debugging and confidence at this scope require first-class observability for every test tier, not ad-hoc println output.\n\nScope\n- Define a versioned observability schema for pane tests: trace_id, event_seq, operation kind, host, pane tree hash, focus/splitter state, timing spans, and failure diagnostics.\n- Define artifact bundle contract for CI/local failures: structured logs (JSONL), replay input trace, normalized snapshots, and metadata manifest.\n- Provide retention/redaction policy for logs so artifacts remain actionable and safe.\n\nAcceptance\n- All pane test harnesses can emit schema-compliant logs and artifact bundles.\n- Failure triage can be performed from artifact bundle without rerunning flaky scenarios.\n- Schema and artifact format are documented and stable for cross-tool consumption.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Implement scoped validation capability with reproducible execution and deterministic assertions.\n2) Add/maintain runner scripts for local+CI with explicit modes (smoke/full/stress) where applicable.\n3) Produce structured logs and artifact bundles (trace, snapshots, metadata) for every failure.\n4) Document pass/fail criteria and ensure outputs are actionable without ad-hoc reruns.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"FoggyPeak","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:47:53.496622656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T06:04:29.650573837Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T06:04:29.650555663Z","close_reason":"Implemented pane observability schema, helper APIs, and pane E2E script wiring with failure artifact manifests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["logging","observability","pane","parity","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-a46q1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-11T05:47:53.496622656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-a46q1.8","title":"task(pane-validation): author reproducible terminal+web E2E runner scripts with verbose diagnostics","description":"Background\n- We need deterministic, ergonomic scripts to run pane E2E suites locally and in CI with rich diagnostics by default.\n\nScope\n- Create canonical runner scripts/commands for terminal PTY E2E and web/wasm E2E, including standard env flags, seed control, timeout policy, and retry semantics.\n- Integrate observability schema/artifact collection so every failure emits trace bundles and concise summary logs.\n- Add command variants for quick smoke, full matrix, and stress modes.\n\nAcceptance\n- Developers can run one documented command per mode and get consistent diagnostics.\n- CI uses the same scripts to avoid local-vs-CI drift.\n- Logs are sufficiently detailed to pinpoint failing interaction step and host context quickly.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Implement scoped validation capability with reproducible execution and deterministic assertions.\n2) Add/maintain runner scripts for local+CI with explicit modes (smoke/full/stress) where applicable.\n3) Produce structured logs and artifact bundles (trace, snapshots, metadata) for every failure.\n4) Document pass/fail criteria and ensure outputs are actionable without ad-hoc reruns.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"FoggyPeak","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-11T05:47:53.854071510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T06:12:45.816425387Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T06:12:45.816406011Z","close_reason":"Added pane terminal+web E2E runner with smoke/full/stress modes, deterministic env controls, and pane trace/artifact-bundle diagnostics; documented commands in README","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","logging","pane","scripts","terminal","test","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-a46q1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-a46q1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-11T05:47:53.85