-{"id":"bd-a46q1.9","title":"task(pane-validation): build traceability matrix mapping every pane bead to unit/e2e/logging evidence","description":"Background\n- To prevent coverage blind spots, each implementation bead must map to explicit verification artifacts before rollout.\n\nScope\n- Create a machine-readable traceability matrix linking each pane feature/task to required unit tests, property/fuzz tests (when applicable), E2E scenarios, and logging artifact expectations.\n- Track evidence status (planned, implemented, passing, flaky, blocked) per mapped item.\n- Integrate matrix checks into rollout gates and CI summaries.\n\nAcceptance\n- Every pane bead under bd-gajnk has explicit test+logging evidence mapping.\n- Missing evidence is surfaced automatically and blocks release-gate completion.\n- Matrix is easy to update as new beads or tests are added.","design":"Verification traceability architecture\n- Treat each pane bead as a requirement node linked to concrete verification artifacts.\n- Evidence links must include exact command/script, artifact location pattern, and expected signal quality.\n- Matrix enables deterministic gap detection before rollout.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Matrix contains entries for every bead under bd-gajnk with required unit/e2e/logging evidence.\n2) Matrix validation fails when mapped evidence is missing, stale, or non-diagnostic.\n3) CI and local workflows can emit matrix-status summaries consistently.\n4) Matrix references canonical script commands, artifact formats, and gate thresholds.","notes":"Planning refinement (2026-02-11):
